Akure – Afeez Smith, a middle-aged man who claimed to be a biological son of former Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Musiliu Smith, has been arraigned before a Chief Magistrate Court sitting in Ondo town for fraud and stealing. The accused was said to have used the name of the former police boss to defraud unsuspecting members of the public in Ondo town. It was learnt that his victims included some policemen serving in the community. The Prosecutor, Olagbayi Bernard, said the accused person recently within the Ondo magisterial district fraudulently obtained a sum of N750,000 from one Fabode Akinsola under the pretence of supplying him one Toyota Corolla car. The accused person was also alleged to have stolen N50, 000, N30, 000 and N200, 020 from Akinlade Ajibola,  Komalafe Abiodun and Akinbobola Olukayode respectively. He was also accused of unlawful possessing one Toyota Venza 2010 model car which he could not give a satisfactory account for. The prosecutor said the offences were contrary to and punishable under section 430, 390, 419 and 383 of the criminal code, cap 37, Volume 1 Laws of Ondo State of Nigeria 2006. The accused, however, pleaded not guilty to all the five-count charges. The presiding Chief Magistrate, Mrs Ajibade B.F, granted the accused person bail who was whisked away by the police when he could not meet the bail conditions. The matter has been adjourned till July 4, 2018, for hearing. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 